# Documentation

- Keep documentation aligned with actual code and commands.
- Use concise examples that can be copied safely.
- Never include real credentials or personal financial information.
- For architecture decisions, capture context, decision, alternatives, consequences, and status.
- Update setup instructions when dependencies, environment variables, ports, or workflows change.
